args: Pray permit me continue my story.

My world did not have the benefit of
mystical travelers. There was no other
version of myself that appeared to grant
us aid and succor.
And that is where the futures\nof our worlds begin to diverge.
Hmm... Perhaps it would be easier to\nunderstand if you consider what would\nhave happened had I not come to you.
Well, for one thing, we probably never\nwould have gone to the Binding Ruins.
No... A fourth pact is sworn.
You're the woman from the forest.
Know that I am not your enemy.
Why do you have a problem with me and\nthe dragons? What's your aim in all this?
But with so many dragons pactbound,\nmy options are limited.
Make for the Binding Ruins. Victory there\nmay yet see this tragedy averted.
I remember that! At the time, I was\npretty sure we couldn't trust you.
But {player_name} said that even\nif it WAS a trap, he'd risk it for his sis.
It's hard to imagine how things would have\nunfolded had we not gone to the ruins.
Yeah, I'm guessin' she's about to tell us.
It is a subtle thing, but like a pebble\nrolling down a hill, so too can one\ntiny change bring down a mountain.
And in my world, my dear brother...
I'm impressed you made it—and at the\nexpense of your friends, no less!\nI didn't think you had it in you.
A bold demand from a man\nwho can barely keep his feet!
Nevertheless, I will grant you a choice.
On your last legs as you are, there is but\none way you can save your sister.
Offer yourself to me as my vessel,\nand I will grant your sister's freedom.
The choice is yours: Die at my hands\nnow, or become my vessel in exchange\nfor your dear sister's life!
I've fought for so long to save Zethia...
And I would gladly trade my life for hers.
Let it be done! Free my sister\nand claim me in her place!
Bwaaaa ha ha ha! Then, my dear brother,\nlet us begin the ritual!
W-we'll meet again, Zethia... I swear...
Heh... Ha! Bwaaaa ha ha ha ha!\nFinally, I have control of a vessel\noverflowing with dragonpacts!
Are you bearing witness, Alberius?\nBehold the fate of the descendant\nyou placed such faith in!
...And with the prince as his vessel,\nhe seized control of all dragons.
They had no choice but to become\nunwilling minions of the Empire.
Please, calm yourself. Your wounds\nare dire—you must let me heal them.
And why would you have me live?\nDoes our suffering please you?
I'm merely trying to save your life.
The Empire slaughtered our families!\nKilled our friends! Burned our homes!
Everything that mattered has been taken\nfrom us, and you would have us LIVE?!
It would be an easy thing for you\nto kill me now, would it not?
You've killed so many people already!\nWhy stop now? What's one more corpse\nadded to your bloody tally?!
No... NO! DON'T HEAL ME!\nI DON'T WANT TO LIVE!
What am I supposed to do now?
(Saving lives is no salvation—not\nin world that has changed so much\nas to choose death over life)
(I may not have been acting of my volition,\nbut as the Other did evil while inside me,\nthe sin is mine to bear.)
I'm a murderer...\nI did such horrible things...

But I know what those people feel.
Everything that matters has also been
taken from me, and it would be so
easy to just let it all...drift away.
W-we'll meet again, Zethia... I swear...
(And until he lives up to that promise,\nI must do all that I can.)
